   <topic id="FAR_9_400">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">9.400</ph> Scope of subpart.</title>
      <body>
         <ol id="d577e13">
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d604e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                   This
subpart-</p>
               <ol id="d577e23">
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d604e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                         Prescribes policies and procedures
governing the debarment and suspension of contractors by agencies
for the causes given in <xref href="9.406-2.dita#FAR_9_406_2"
                              base="i1115334"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.406-2</xref> and <xref href="9.407-2.dita#FAR_9_407_2"
                              base="i1115483"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.407-2</xref>;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d604e27">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                         Provides
for the listing of contractors debarred, suspended, proposed for
debarment, and declared ineligible (see the definition of "ineligible"
in <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                              base="i1125359"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">2.101</xref>); and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d604e35">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                         Sets forth
the consequences of this listing.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d604e40">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                   Although
this subpart does cover the listing of ineligible contractors (<xref href="9.404.dita#FAR_9_404"
                        base="i1115204"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.404</xref>) and the effect
of this listing (<xref href="9.405.dita#FAR_9_405"
                        base="i1115236"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.405</xref>), it does not
prescribe policies and procedures governing declarations of ineligibility
except for contractors that have been declared ineligible pursuant
to <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section983&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 983 </xref>(see <xref href="9.110.dita#FAR_9_110" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.110</xref>,
and <xref href="9.405-1.dita#FAR_9_405_1" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.405-1</xref>(b)).</p>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d606e60">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> For Federal Acquisition Supply Chain Security Act (FASCSA) orders, see subpart <xref href="Subpart_4.23.dita#FAR_Subpart_4_23" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">4.23</xref>. </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </body>
   </topic>
